{"data":{"markdownRemark":{"fields":{"slug":"/docs/guide/sidebar"},"id":"c372c32b-0319-517b-b91f-e547acd93f32","html":"<h2 id=\"introduction\"><a href=\"#introduction\" aria-label=\"introduction permalink\" class=\"post-toc-anchor\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Introduction</h2>\n<p>The sidebar is automatically generated with a given <code>sidebar</code> entry from the current page, where the information are stored in the corresponding markdown file (see <a href=\"/docs/guide/contents#information-of-the-page\">contents</a>). All the entries of this example are defined in the file <code>/src/sidebars/sidebars.json</code>. And it will list all the pages under the given <code>sidebar</code> entry.</p>\n<p>By default, only the selected page will be expanded on the sidebar.</p>\n<h2 id=\"format\"><a href=\"#format\" aria-label=\"format permalink\" class=\"post-toc-anchor\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Format</h2>\n<p>All the entries are defined in json format, and it must be an array of objects. For each object must includes:</p>\n<ul>\n<li><code>entry</code>: an unique entry of the object</li>\n<li><code>name</code>: the name will be shown on the sidebar (does not need to be unique)</li>\n</ul>\n<p>And for different layouts, it might include:</p>\n<ul>\n<li><code>child_entries</code>: a list of the entries under the current entry</li>\n<li><code>items</code>: a list of the post paths</li>\n</ul>\n<h3 id=\"one-level-example\"><a href=\"#one-level-example\" aria-label=\"one level example permalink\" class=\"post-toc-anchor\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>One-level Example</h3>\n<p>For single level sidebar (e.g. <a href=\"/blog/first-blog\">blog</a>):</p>\n<pre><code class=\"language-json\">{\n  \"entry\": \"Blog\",\n  \"name\": \"Blog\",\n  \"items\": [\n    \"blog/first-blog\",\n    \"blog/second-blog\"\n  ]\n}\n</code></pre>\n<p>The sidebar only contains two posts (i.e. <code>items</code> listed in json)</p>","frontmatter":{"date":null,"title":"Sidebar","sidebar":"Docs","showTitle":true}}},"pageContext":{"isCreatedByStatefulCreatePages":false}}